latestIgtvVideos.title: Surya Namaskar on the ocassion of INTERNATIONAL YOGA DAY
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hi guys..On the ocassion of IYD I would like to share my favourite youga exercise... Here goes the step description along with the name of the poses.. 12 Step  Surya Namaskar on the ocassion of INTERNATIONAL YOGA DAY:-⁣⁣⠀
Step 1: Prayer pose – Pranamasana.⁣⠀
⁣⠀
Step 2: Raised arms pose – Hastauttanasana.⁣⠀
⁣⠀
Step 3: Hand to foot pose – Hasta Padasana. ⁣⠀
⁣⁣⠀
Step 4: Equestrian pose – Ashwa Sanchalanasana. ⁣⠀
⁣⠀
Step 5: Stick pose – Dandasana. ⁣⠀
⁣⠀
Step 6: Salute with eight parts or points – Ashtanga Namaskara. ⁣⠀
⁣⠀
Step 7: Cobra pose – Bhujangasana.⁣⁣⠀
⁣⠀
Step 8: Mountain pose – Parvatasana.⁣⠀
⁣⁣⠀
Step 9: Equestrian pose – Ashwa Sanchalanasana⁣.⁣⠀
⁣⠀
Step 10: Hand to foot pose – Hasta Padasana⁣.⁣⠀
⁣⠀
Step 11: Raised Arms Pose- Hastauttanasana⁣.⁣⠀
⁣⠀
Step 12: Prayer pose – Pranamasana. ⁣⠀
⁣⁣⠀
⁣⠀
⁣⁣⠀
To reap the maximum benefits of this exercise, perform 12 sets of these asanas every day, that is six rounds on the right leg and six rounds on the left leg.⁣⁣⠀
⁣⠀
⁣⁣⠀
Benefits:-⁣⁣⠀
The Surya Namaskar practice stretches the abdominal muscles and helps to reduce excess weight and fat around your stomach. Moreover, it also helps to tone your arms, abs, and brings flexibility to your spine. Stress reducing agent: The Surya Namaskar helps to reduce stress and improve memory and nervous system. .
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Happy Earth Day 🌅💐🌍🌈..
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
The coronavirus has incited a lot of change across the world these last couple months. Entire cities have shut down, trains and airfare have all but nearly stopped, public spaces are shut down, concerts cancelled, ski resorts closed. Much of life has come to a stop—as have much of the world’s output of greenhouse gases.

If there’s something good to come from this worldwide pandemic, it might be the way Earth is given a chance to breathe a bit. Scientists have already seen how quickly the climate, and nature far and wide, is already revitalizing and recovering from human climate change damage.

This is a beautiful message by @luxurionworld  on the ocassion of Earth Day.. Mother Nature is healing its own way ..
Hope we  understand the gravity of the situation and once we overcome this pandemic situation we come together and take care of our mother nature the way it deserves... Happy Earth Day. Stay healthy .Stay safe everyone 🌍💐🌅💕❤️🎉🙏 #pandemic2020  #happyearthday🌎 #covid_19 #lockdown #lockdown2020 #pandemiclife #quarantinelife #quarantine #motherearth #nature #naturelovers #gocoronago #coronavirus #stayhome #staysafeeveryone #stayhealthy #stayathome #staystrong #instagood #instadaily #instamood #instacool

Embracing the six yards of elegance from @teejhindia , the saree becomes more than just a garment—it transforms into a symbol of grace and tradition. 

Paired with intricately crafted silver jewelry, it adds an aura of timeless charm, reflecting the artistry and culture embedded in Kolkata’s soul.

Wearing this ensemble at Kolkata’s iconic places,I find myself standing against the iconic backdrop of Kolkata’s heritage. The Howrah Bridge, a marvel of engineering, looms majestically above, connecting the city’s past and present with every steel beam. 
Beneath its shadows lies the bustling Mallick Ghat Flower Market, where vibrant hues of marigolds and roses reflect Kolkata’s deep-rooted traditions and enduring beauty.
As the Tram slowly glides through the city, I am reminded of Kolkata’s old-world charm. The rhythmic clatter of its wheels echoes the stories of a bygone era, while the heritage and culture of the city live on in every turn. 
In this timeless space, the saree flows effortlessly, embodying grace, history, and the rich cultural tapestry that is uniquely Kolkata.
Here, tradition isn’t just worn—it is celebrated.

In this city where every street tells a story and every moment is a celebration of culture, I honor the beautiful blend of history, artistry, and joy that makes Kolkata truly unforgettable.

Saree: @teejhindia 
Blouse: @sazrikafashion 
Accessories: @teejhindia 
Heels: @inc5official 

Shot by : @i_m_d810 
📍Location: Mallick Ghat Flower Market

Jamai Sasthi vibes in full swing! 🍛🍗🥘🍨💛 

Taking over the pampering duties since maa couldn’t make it to Bangalore this time. 

From extra mishti to endless love, making sure her jamai doesn’t miss the Kolkata touch! 

Tradition, food, and a whole lot of warmth—because some rituals are too sweet to skip 🥰🍛🎉 (Jamai Sasthi is a Bengali tradition where the son-in-law is pampered with love, blessings, and a grand feast). 

Huge thanks to @grandmercuregopalanmall for arranging this so beautifully and having us over—it truly felt like home away from home! 🙏✨

Step into a world of royal flavours at Spice Terrace, @jwmarriottblr , as the Rampuri Festival comes alive from 23rd May to 1st June.

Curated by the renowned Khansama Nasir Hussain, who brings over 30 years of culinary mastery from the royal kitchens of Rampur, this festival is a tribute to one of India’s most refined and lesser-known cuisines. From aromatic taark korma and sambhal seekh to the indulgent Mirchi ka Halwa — each dish is steeped in heritage, crafted with rare ingredients like ittar and traditional spice blends.

Don’t miss this limited-time celebration of authentic Rampuri delicacies served with timeless elegance, right in the heart of the city.
